>    den = cos(x2) + cosh(y2);
>    r->r = sin(x2)/den;
>    /* any limit above about log(DBL_EPSILON) will do */
>    if (fabs(r->i) < 40.0)

You need z->i (or y2) here, r->i hasn't been initialized yet. Otherwise, 
yes.


